txt.en: You should talk to Tuhâl, who can be found in Utterby.
'You are kinder than the Jangovar. Thank you.'
'I will live another day, thanks to you.'
'Thank you for this kindness, stranger. I will escape when I can.'
The Jangovar have been holding what food there is for themselves, leaving many to starve. Give food to the hungry refugees so they can flee the village.

'The Jangovar have been holding what food there is for themselves, leaving many to starve. Now that we have some food, we should give it to those most in need. It should give them strength enough to flee this terrible place.'
Many of the refugees are starving, as the Jangovar hold all the food for themselves.\n\nYou should offer food to hungry refugees.
'They were so grateful just to receive a few scraps of food.... The sooner we get out of here, the better.'
